# Navigation and UI Fixes Walkthrough

## Overview
This update focused on resolving compilation errors, improving the navigation flow, and enhancing the visual design of the Launch Button.

## Changes

### 1. Fixed Compilation Errors
- **`CS0272` (Property Access)**: The `NavigationView.SelectedItem` setter was inaccessible. We resolved this by exposing a public [NavigateTo(string tag)](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs#165-192) method in [MainWindow.xaml.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml.cs).
- **`MC3072` (XAML Property)**: Fixed `IsPaneToggleButtonVisible` error in [MainWindow.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/MainWindow.xaml) by renaming it to `IsPaneToggleVisible`.

### 2. UI/UX Improvements
- **Hamburger Menu Removal**: Hidden the hamburger menu in the sidebar (`IsPaneToggleVisible="False"`).
- **Launch Button Aesthetic**: 
  - Transformed the "Start Game" button into a full "Pill" shape (`CornerRadius="30"`) with a vibrant green gradient and shadow.
  - Increased font size and added a rocket icon for a more "complete" and premium look.
  - Aligned the loading progress bar overlay to match the new button shape.
- **Functional Buttons**:
  - Wired up "Go to Download Page" and "Version Selection" buttons to correctly navigate to their respective pages.

## Verification
- **Build**: The application should build successfully.
- **Visuals**: The Launch Button should now look like a rounded pill with a smooth green gradient, appearing "complete" and polished.
- **Navigation**: Verify all sidebar and internal buttons navigate as expected.

## Next Steps
- Continue implementing the Export functionality and other pending features.
